<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-03-10T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-03-10T11:00:00-05:00" n="197" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d197">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.20 Mission/3–1048: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-03-10T11:00:00-05:00">March 10, 1948—11
                                a.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>378. Your 425 of March 7 refers. I stand completely corrected. All of us
                            here, Army included, had lost sight of Deptel 1302. My abject apologies
                            to all concerned. I was delighted to get your reaction to Barr’s
                            performance.</p>
                        <p>Army tells me they authorized him to proceed on this matter within 24
                            hours of receipt of request.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>